00:20:17.580 --> 00:20:21.830 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes guides will say you
need to take more time just

00:20:21.830 --> 00:20:27.260 align:middle line:84%
to go do what you want to do and
not pressure yourself so much.

00:20:27.260 --> 00:20:31.080 align:middle line:84%
And so it's all about learning,
who are we at the core level?

00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:34.520 align:middle line:84%
Not just who are
we in life today?

00:20:34.520 --> 00:20:38.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And speaking of
today, so let's maybe if you can

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:41.120 align:middle line:84%
reflect back on a client
or share a story with us,

00:20:41.120 --> 00:20:42.940 align:middle line:90%
yours or someone else's.

00:20:42.940 --> 00:20:46.370 align:middle line:84%
Often what happens in past
life regression, of course,

00:20:46.370 --> 00:20:49.910 align:middle line:84%
is they're not necessarily going
to bring you a linear past life.

00:20:49.910 --> 00:20:51.910 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
bring a past life that

00:20:51.910 --> 00:20:54.400 align:middle line:84%
is directly reflective
of what you're working

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:56.570 align:middle line:90%
on enhancing or learning now.

00:20:56.570 --> 00:20:59.470 align:middle line:84%
And that could have been
thousands of years ago.

00:20:59.470 --> 00:21:04.780 align:middle line:84%
Oh, so please talk about that
and share a regression or two

00:21:04.780 --> 00:21:06.680 align:middle line:84%
about this, because
people are confused.

00:21:06.680 --> 00:21:08.630 align:middle line:84%
They think it's their
immediate last life.

00:21:08.630 --> 00:21:10.160 align:middle line:90%
No, that's not how it works.

00:21:10.160 --> 00:21:11.090 align:middle line:90%
It's non-linear.

00:21:11.090 --> 00:21:12.560 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Well, two things.

00:21:12.560 --> 00:21:15.760 align:middle line:84%
It's almost never your
most recent past life.

00:21:15.760 --> 00:21:21.260 align:middle line:84%
And just so listeners know
this, lives can overlap in time.

00:21:21.260 --> 00:21:25.370 align:middle line:84%
So that kind of sets up
a bit of a confusion.

00:21:25.370 --> 00:21:30.020 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I mean, I love
our organic conversation.

00:21:30.020 --> 00:21:34.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm flashing on a recent client.

00:21:34.210 --> 00:21:37.480 align:middle line:84%
I can't tell you how long
ago this was, but when I tell

00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:38.740 align:middle line:90%
the details, it'll be obvious.

00:21:38.740 --> 00:21:39.880 align:middle line:90%
It was a long time ago.

00:21:39.880 --> 00:21:43.680 align:middle line:84%
This woman, one of the reasons
for coming for the regression is

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:46.980 align:middle line:84%
she said, I'm very
spiritual, but I've always

00:21:46.980 --> 00:21:47.910 align:middle line:90%
been afraid of dying.

00:21:47.910 --> 00:21:50.140 align:middle line:90%
And I just can't seem to shake.

00:21:50.140 --> 00:21:51.730 align:middle line:90%
I know we continue.

00:21:51.730 --> 00:21:53.940 align:middle line:90%
I know our soul is immortal.

00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:56.720 align:middle line:90%
But I have such a fear of dying.

00:21:56.720 --> 00:21:59.710 align:middle line:84%
And I think listeners know
when I'm guiding regression,

00:21:59.710 --> 00:22:03.810 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea before the
regression where it's going.

00:22:03.810 --> 00:22:08.420 align:middle line:84%
She went into-- it's fascinating
for me and hopefully fascinating

00:22:08.420 --> 00:22:09.220 align:middle line:90%
for the client.

00:22:09.220 --> 00:22:13.680 align:middle line:84%
She went into a time
of living in a cave.

00:22:13.680 --> 00:22:15.220 align:middle line:90%
She was a leper.

00:22:15.220 --> 00:22:16.600 align:middle line:90%
She had leprosy.

00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:20.700 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sure we're talking
thousands of years ago.

00:22:20.700 --> 00:22:26.610 align:middle line:84%
She was a leper in a cave with
a man who was also had leprosy.

00:22:26.610 --> 00:22:30.340 align:middle line:84%
They weren't romantically
connected with each other.

00:22:30.340 --> 00:22:33.060 align:middle line:84%
They were living in
this cave because they

00:22:33.060 --> 00:22:36.740 align:middle line:84%
were protecting other
people from their disease.

00:22:36.740 --> 00:22:39.180 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, she was not
in the cave by herself,

00:22:39.180 --> 00:22:41.210 align:middle line:84%
but she learned
how she died, which

00:22:41.210 --> 00:22:44.780 align:middle line:84%
was the release valve,
almost like the release

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:46.410 align:middle line:90%
valve on a pressure cooker.

00:22:46.410 --> 00:22:51.870 align:middle line:84%
So she discovered that there was
a major storm or a major flood

00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:56.510 align:middle line:84%
or something, and
the cave flooded.

00:22:56.510 --> 00:22:58.770 align:middle line:84%
And this may sound
awful to listeners.

00:22:58.770 --> 00:23:01.350 align:middle line:84%
It was a complete
release for her.

00:23:01.350 --> 00:23:06.030 align:middle line:84%
The cave flooded and she died
because the cave flooded.

00:23:06.030 --> 00:23:09.390 align:middle line:90%
That was the fear of dying.

00:23:09.390 --> 00:23:13.340 align:middle line:84%
She reported to me after
days and a few weeks

00:23:13.340 --> 00:23:16.400 align:middle line:84%
after the regression
that she had released

00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:19.880 align:middle line:84%
her fear of dying because
she understood what happened

00:23:19.880 --> 00:23:21.120 align:middle line:90%
thousands of years ago.

00:23:21.120 --> 00:23:23.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did she also
have a fear of water?

00:23:23.390 --> 00:23:24.196 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yeah.

00:23:24.196 --> 00:23:26.654 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A lot of people have
a fear of water when they've

00:23:26.654 --> 00:23:27.960 align:middle line:90%
drowned a number of times.

00:23:27.960 --> 00:23:28.760 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Exactly.

00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:31.040 align:middle line:84%
I think it was a
fear, basically,

00:23:31.040 --> 00:23:36.820 align:middle line:84%
of dying because water
and mud filled the cave.

00:23:36.820 --> 00:23:40.940 align:middle line:84%
And so people might go, oh,
dear, that's really awful.

00:23:40.940 --> 00:23:44.030 align:middle line:84%
What I teach people how
to guide regression.

00:23:44.030 --> 00:23:48.310 align:middle line:84%
And what I say is you've got
to be supportive and stay

00:23:48.310 --> 00:23:54.370 align:middle line:84%
with the client, because the
ultimate release will almost

00:23:54.370 --> 00:23:57.730 align:middle line:90%
always alleviate the fear.

00:23:57.730 --> 00:23:58.850 align:middle line:90%
And it did.

00:23:58.850 --> 00:24:02.270 align:middle line:84%
But it was fascinating that
she could see she was a leper.

00:24:02.270 --> 00:24:03.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow, that's wonderful.

00:24:03.730 --> 00:24:08.290 align:middle line:84%
When you're talking, one thing
that's striking me is I've

00:24:08.290 --> 00:24:10.850 align:middle line:90%
always had this feeling.

00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:13.640 align:middle line:84%
And I guess, I don't know
if it's a fear or not

00:24:13.640 --> 00:24:19.540 align:middle line:84%
a fear, maybe, of dying
at a certain time of day.

00:24:19.540 --> 00:24:22.990 align:middle line:84%
And it happens to
be the time of day

00:24:22.990 --> 00:24:28.340 align:middle line:84%
I was born in this lifetime
with the sun at that angle.

00:24:28.340 --> 00:24:32.320 align:middle line:84%
And then many years
later, I learned that

00:24:32.320 --> 00:24:34.560 align:middle line:84%
through the
Rosicrucian teachings

00:24:34.560 --> 00:24:37.410 align:middle line:84%
that they believe that
your time of birth

00:24:37.410 --> 00:24:42.180 align:middle line:84%
coincides with the time of
death in your last incarnation.

00:24:42.180 --> 00:24:44.178 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
that's interesting.

00:24:44.178 --> 00:24:45.720 align:middle line:84%
I wonder what was
going on, because I

00:24:45.720 --> 00:24:50.400 align:middle line:84%
remember thinking I would
rather die earlier in the day

00:24:50.400 --> 00:24:51.330 align:middle line:90%
than then.

00:24:51.330 --> 00:24:54.010 align:middle line:84%
And Always I've carried that
feeling with me my whole life.

00:24:54.010 --> 00:24:55.870 align:middle line:84%
So when I see the light
at that time of day,

00:24:55.870 --> 00:24:58.120 align:middle line:84%
it's like, yeah, I
don't like that light.

00:24:58.120 --> 00:25:00.750 align:middle line:84%
So something must
have happened in the--

00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:01.953 align:middle line:90%
and I never looked into it.

00:25:01.953 --> 00:25:04.120 align:middle line:84%
I've never regressed myself
or been regressed on it.

00:25:04.120 --> 00:25:06.680 align:middle line:90%
But I find that interesting.

00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:09.607 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: I've never heard
that Rosicrucian belief.

00:25:09.607 --> 00:25:11.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's somewhere
in the Hermetic teachings was

00:25:11.940 --> 00:25:13.350 align:middle line:90%
talking about that, I thought.

00:25:13.350 --> 00:25:15.250 align:middle line:84%
It was a Rosicrucian
book, actually.

00:25:15.250 --> 00:25:17.310 align:middle line:84%
I thought that's
interesting that we

00:25:17.310 --> 00:25:20.140 align:middle line:84%
would pick up on the
frequency we left off at.

00:25:20.140 --> 00:25:22.720 align:middle line:84%
If that's true, I only
read it in one book.

00:25:22.720 --> 00:25:25.710 align:middle line:84%
So it's hearsay
until we find out

00:25:25.710 --> 00:25:28.810 align:middle line:84%
on a mass scale people are
experiencing this, I suppose.

00:25:28.810 --> 00:25:33.070 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: But that would be
fascinating to theoretically

00:25:33.070 --> 00:25:39.700 align:middle line:84%
guide you in a regression, not
necessarily to see at what time

00:25:39.700 --> 00:25:42.160 align:middle line:90%
of day that might come forward.

00:25:42.160 --> 00:25:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: 4:44.

00:25:44.530 --> 00:25:45.705 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: So it's 4:44.

00:25:45.705 --> 00:25:47.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In the
afternoon, yeah.

00:25:47.080 --> 00:25:47.880 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yeah.

00:25:47.880 --> 00:25:49.750 align:middle line:84%
So there's probably
some numerology,

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:50.990 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure you know this.

00:25:50.990 --> 00:25:54.830 align:middle line:84%
There's some kind of
numerology relationship.

00:25:54.830 --> 00:25:57.775 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure you know
numbers have meaning.

00:25:57.775 --> 00:25:59.420 align:middle line:90%
And so that's the case.

00:25:59.420 --> 00:26:06.700 align:middle line:84%
But to ask, that's the beauty
of discovering and asking

00:26:06.700 --> 00:26:08.320 align:middle line:84%
questions in the
longer regression

00:26:08.320 --> 00:26:10.700 align:middle line:84%
that I guide, which is
also soul level regression,

00:26:10.700 --> 00:26:13.340 align:middle line:84%
is for what reason
do I have this worry?

00:26:13.340 --> 00:26:18.320 align:middle line:84%
For what reason do I look at the
sun at 4:44 and wonder what that

00:26:18.320 --> 00:26:19.120 align:middle line:90%
means?

00:26:19.120 --> 00:26:21.740 align:middle line:90%
I know for me, I have many--

00:26:21.740 --> 00:26:23.590 align:middle line:84%
I have far more
than one past life

00:26:23.590 --> 00:26:26.450 align:middle line:84%
where I died young
from an illness.

00:26:26.450 --> 00:26:30.400 align:middle line:84%
And young, meaning younger
in my adult years than I

00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:31.820 align:middle line:90%
would have expected to die.

00:26:31.820 --> 00:26:42.600 align:middle line:84%
And I died from a deteriorating
illness, that worry lives in me.

00:26:42.600 --> 00:26:44.050 align:middle line:90%
So it's not fully gone.

00:26:44.050 --> 00:26:46.440 align:middle line:84%
But because I know
about it, it helps

00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:51.910 align:middle line:84%
me to not let physical
things overly concern me.

00:26:51.910 --> 00:26:54.360 align:middle line:90%
So I think a lot of us have.

00:26:54.360 --> 00:26:55.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:57.690 align:middle line:84%
And as you're
speaking about that,

00:26:57.690 --> 00:27:00.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm feeling like
what bothers me about

00:27:00.360 --> 00:27:02.140 align:middle line:84%
that, I think I live
to be quite old,

00:27:02.140 --> 00:27:04.210 align:middle line:84%
which I may again
in this lifetime.

00:27:04.210 --> 00:27:08.730 align:middle line:84%
And I think I was alone
when the sun was setting.

00:27:08.730 --> 00:27:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And it's something about
the kind of a coldness

00:27:12.810 --> 00:27:19.650 align:middle line:84%
and a loneliness of those last
hours of awareness as the sun is

00:27:19.650 --> 00:27:22.450 align:middle line:90%
setting, something about that.

00:27:22.450 --> 00:27:25.200 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: So my sense is,
and this is the beauty

00:27:25.200 --> 00:27:28.020 align:middle line:84%
of our conversation right
now, is that my sense is

00:27:28.020 --> 00:27:30.300 align:middle line:84%
you're tapping into
valid information.

00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:32.403 align:middle line:90%
That's how it feels to me.

00:27:32.403 --> 00:27:34.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, because
that's one thing

00:27:34.070 --> 00:27:35.760 align:middle line:90%
about living to be really old.

00:27:35.760 --> 00:27:37.830 align:middle line:84%
We also want to
have a long life.

00:27:37.830 --> 00:27:39.680 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times,
those last years

00:27:39.680 --> 00:27:41.130 align:middle line:90%
are very lonely for people.

00:27:41.130 --> 00:27:43.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm so glad my dad
lived into his 90s.

00:27:43.380 --> 00:27:45.230 align:middle line:84%
I'm so glad we could
be there for him

00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:47.180 align:middle line:90%
right up to the very end.

00:27:47.180 --> 00:27:51.810 align:middle line:84%
To be surrounded with love
is such a wonderful luxury,

00:27:51.810 --> 00:27:54.620 align:middle line:90%
if you can have that.

00:27:54.620 --> 00:27:57.860 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: So that brings
forward another quick story.

00:27:57.860 --> 00:27:58.710 align:middle line:90%
Quick story.

00:27:58.710 --> 00:28:02.510 align:middle line:84%
My mother died at 93
about 10 years ago.

00:28:02.510 --> 00:28:04.730 align:middle line:90%
My mother and I did not have--

00:28:04.730 --> 00:28:07.320 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we had a relationship
throughout my whole life,

00:28:07.320 --> 00:28:09.720 align:middle line:84%
but my mother was not
an easy personality.

00:28:09.720 --> 00:28:12.000 align:middle line:84%
And lots of people
agreed with that.

00:28:12.000 --> 00:28:14.910 align:middle line:84%
But as she was getting older
and once she was a widow,

00:28:14.910 --> 00:28:18.560 align:middle line:84%
after my father passed,
I had this compulsion

00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:23.450 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't understand to
make sure she was cared for.

00:28:23.450 --> 00:28:26.300 align:middle line:84%
And I was going to be
the one versus my sibling

00:28:26.300 --> 00:28:28.080 align:middle line:90%
to make sure mom was cared for.

00:28:28.080 --> 00:28:33.560 align:middle line:84%
So that happened, and we had
her in a very wonderful facility

00:28:33.560 --> 00:28:36.040 align:middle line:84%
and I visited her
at least once a week

00:28:36.040 --> 00:28:41.020 align:middle line:84%
and made sure her needs were
met, et cetera, Et cetera.

00:28:41.020 --> 00:28:45.220 align:middle line:84%
In that course of that period
of time, seven or eight years,

00:28:45.220 --> 00:28:48.310 align:middle line:84%
we finally said I love
you to each other.

00:28:48.310 --> 00:28:52.100 align:middle line:84%
She didn't expect me to want
to take care of her, and I did.

00:28:52.100 --> 00:28:54.340 align:middle line:84%
But in the course of
the seven or eight years

00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:58.060 align:middle line:84%
that she lived in this
very wonderful facility

00:28:58.060 --> 00:29:02.320 align:middle line:84%
not too far from where I live,
I discovered a past life.

00:29:02.320 --> 00:29:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered a
past life of mine

00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:08.180 align:middle line:84%
where, to make the
long story short,

00:29:08.180 --> 00:29:13.210 align:middle line:84%
I was married to a man that
had political aspirations.

00:29:13.210 --> 00:29:14.960 align:middle line:90%
This life was in India.

00:29:14.960 --> 00:29:17.420 align:middle line:84%
I was married to a man that
had political aspirations.

00:29:17.420 --> 00:29:18.680 align:middle line:90%
I deeply loved this man.

00:29:18.680 --> 00:29:22.060 align:middle line:90%
He was much older than I was.

00:29:22.060 --> 00:29:23.440 align:middle line:90%
So we married.

00:29:23.440 --> 00:29:25.490 align:middle line:84%
My family didn't
want me to marry him.

00:29:25.490 --> 00:29:27.560 align:middle line:90%
I was Zoroastrian.

00:29:27.560 --> 00:29:33.250 align:middle line:84%
I was of the Persian
faith and he was Muslim.

00:29:33.250 --> 00:29:37.510 align:middle line:84%
And in order to marry him,
I had to convert to Islam.

00:29:37.510 --> 00:29:38.920 align:middle line:90%
And my family did not like that.

00:29:38.920 --> 00:29:41.200 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, I was
deeply in love with him.

00:29:41.200 --> 00:29:42.480 align:middle line:90%
We had a daughter.

00:29:42.480 --> 00:29:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And soon after the
daughter was born,

00:29:45.990 --> 00:29:51.100 align:middle line:84%
he basically left the marriage
for his political desires.

00:29:51.100 --> 00:29:56.110 align:middle line:84%
I was so bereft over this
that when our daughter was 10,

00:29:56.110 --> 00:29:58.630 align:middle line:84%
I willed myself to
die from an illness.

00:29:58.630 --> 00:30:01.360 align:middle line:90%
But I willed myself to die.

00:30:01.360 --> 00:30:06.430 align:middle line:84%
The soul of the daughter is the
soul of my current life mother.

00:30:06.430 --> 00:30:10.800 align:middle line:84%
So it explained why I needed
to clean up the karma.

00:30:10.800 --> 00:30:13.080 align:middle line:84%
She'd already been
abandoned by her father.

00:30:13.080 --> 00:30:17.170 align:middle line:84%
So I abandoned her by
dying when she was 10.

00:30:17.170 --> 00:30:22.870 align:middle line:84%
And it helped me understand the
compulsion to take care of mom,

00:30:22.870 --> 00:30:25.163 align:middle line:90%
which I'm so glad I did.

00:30:25.163 --> 00:30:26.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To just
get to the point

00:30:26.580 --> 00:30:28.250 align:middle line:84%
where you could say I
love you to each other.

00:30:28.250 --> 00:30:30.792 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: Well, I was with her
when she took her last breath.

00:30:30.792 --> 00:30:32.260 align:middle line:90%
It's exactly what I wanted.

00:30:32.260 --> 00:30:34.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's wonderful.

00:30:34.090 --> 00:30:38.920 align:middle line:84%
So in a cell maturation level,
as families go through this

00:30:38.920 --> 00:30:40.880 align:middle line:90%
and mature together, we do.

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:44.350 align:middle line:84%
We do have a time where we
start splitting off a bit,

00:30:44.350 --> 00:30:48.040 align:middle line:84%
where I talked about
early on, and we

00:30:48.040 --> 00:30:51.160 align:middle line:84%
start taking on new
members of our soul tribe

00:30:51.160 --> 00:30:53.750 align:middle line:84%
to be able to engage us
into these new lessons.

00:30:53.750 --> 00:30:55.600 align:middle line:84%
So in our other
conversations, we've

00:30:55.600 --> 00:30:57.730 align:middle line:84%
talked about the three
main groups that are here--

00:30:57.730 --> 00:31:00.410 align:middle line:84%
Earth-based souls, IP
interplanetary souls,

00:31:00.410 --> 00:31:01.670 align:middle line:90%
and angelic type souls.

00:31:01.670 --> 00:31:04.840 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
what that looks

00:31:04.840 --> 00:31:07.390 align:middle line:84%
like with Earth-based
souls, which

00:31:07.390 --> 00:31:09.400 align:middle line:90%
are the majority of people.

00:31:09.400 --> 00:31:11.980 align:middle line:84%
How those family
dynamics, what you

00:31:11.980 --> 00:31:14.560 align:middle line:84%
see in terms of the
transformation and growth

00:31:14.560 --> 00:31:18.980 align:middle line:84%
and the need to move beyond
that particular soul family

00:31:18.980 --> 00:31:20.590 align:middle line:84%
perchance, or at
least some of them

00:31:20.590 --> 00:31:23.120 align:middle line:84%
compared to some of
the IP souls coming in.

00:31:23.120 --> 00:31:24.200 align:middle line:90%
That's a whole different.

00:31:24.200 --> 00:31:25.000 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yeah.

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:27.520 align:middle line:84%
And soul families are different,
which we can talk about.

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:30.750 align:middle line:84%
So families are different for
interplanetary and angelic

00:31:30.750 --> 00:31:31.823 align:middle line:90%
souls.

00:31:31.823 --> 00:31:34.240 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about Earth-based
first and then the other two.

00:31:34.240 --> 00:31:37.900 align:middle line:84%
So Earth-based souls,
when our soul is new,

00:31:37.900 --> 00:31:42.600 align:middle line:84%
we are a member of what I call
soul pod of a good friend that

00:31:42.600 --> 00:31:45.190 align:middle line:84%
calls it a soul posse,
which is an interesting way.

00:31:45.190 --> 00:31:46.800 align:middle line:90%
So a soul pod.

00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:51.160 align:middle line:84%
An Earth-based soul pod
is about 12 to 20 souls,

00:31:51.160 --> 00:31:56.010 align:middle line:84%
and we have more lives with
those souls in that soul

00:31:56.010 --> 00:31:58.720 align:middle line:90%
pod than any other souls.

00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:02.235 align:middle line:84%
And then secondarily,
we have the next,

00:32:02.235 --> 00:32:03.610 align:middle line:84%
this is always
hard to verbalize,

00:32:03.610 --> 00:32:05.650 align:middle line:90%
we have the next most--

00:32:05.650 --> 00:32:10.390 align:middle line:84%
the next greatest number of
lives with adjacent soul pods.

00:32:10.390 --> 00:32:12.820 align:middle line:90%
Our soul pod never changes.

00:32:12.820 --> 00:32:16.720 align:middle line:84%
It is what it is,
but it can be unique.

00:32:16.720 --> 00:32:20.280 align:middle line:84%
Like for example, it just so
happens that my husband and I

00:32:20.280 --> 00:32:21.520 align:middle line:90%
are in the same soul pod.

00:32:21.520 --> 00:32:24.150 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't happen
for all people--

00:32:24.150 --> 00:32:26.880 align:middle line:84%
of romantically
connected people.

00:32:26.880 --> 00:32:29.670 align:middle line:84%
One of his grandparents
is in the pod

00:32:29.670 --> 00:32:32.710 align:middle line:84%
and one of my grandparents
is in the pod.

00:32:32.710 --> 00:32:37.470 align:middle line:84%
So in other words, it isn't
just, oh, it's my mother

00:32:37.470 --> 00:32:40.870 align:middle line:84%
and my mother's mother
and my grandfather.

00:32:40.870 --> 00:32:46.780 align:middle line:84%
It can be someone else's
loved ones, if you will.

00:32:46.780 --> 00:32:49.800 align:middle line:84%
And of course, those
people in that soul pod

00:32:49.800 --> 00:32:51.900 align:middle line:84%
don't always incarnate
in every life.

00:32:51.900 --> 00:32:54.840 align:middle line:90%
So they're not all with us now.

00:32:54.840 --> 00:32:58.290 align:middle line:84%
And they also may be people
that are not our family

00:32:58.290 --> 00:33:00.840 align:middle line:90%
members in current life.

00:33:00.840 --> 00:33:02.747 align:middle line:90%
But the soul pod doesn't change.

00:33:02.747 --> 00:33:03.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: All right.

00:33:03.580 --> 00:33:06.220 align:middle line:84%
So you have your set people
and then your adjacent,

00:33:06.220 --> 00:33:07.620 align:middle line:84%
which is kind of
compatible where

00:33:07.620 --> 00:33:09.940 align:middle line:84%
they come in and
out in incarnations,

00:33:09.940 --> 00:33:11.940 align:middle line:90%
your adjacent soul pod?

00:33:11.940 --> 00:33:16.530 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: The adjacent, quick
example would be I have two

00:33:16.530 --> 00:33:17.470 align:middle line:90%
children.

00:33:17.470 --> 00:33:20.530 align:middle line:84%
Our oldest child is
in the pod I'm in.

00:33:20.530 --> 00:33:22.930 align:middle line:84%
Our younger child is
in an adjacent pod.

00:33:22.930 --> 00:33:25.390 align:middle line:84%
It just means that with
our younger child that's

00:33:25.390 --> 00:33:28.990 align:middle line:84%
our daughter, I haven't had
quite as many lives with her

00:33:28.990 --> 00:33:30.290 align:middle line:90%
as our son.

00:33:30.290 --> 00:33:32.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, let's
get to the eyepiece,

00:33:32.450 --> 00:33:35.180 align:middle line:90%
the interplanetary soul pods.

00:33:35.180 --> 00:33:36.640 align:middle line:90%
How does that even work?

00:33:36.640 --> 00:33:41.420 align:middle line:84%
These souls have come in
from around the cosmos.

00:33:41.420 --> 00:33:42.220 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yes.

00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:45.770 align:middle line:84%
So interplanetary
soul pods are small.

00:33:45.770 --> 00:33:49.520 align:middle line:84%
They're usually
three to five souls.

00:33:49.520 --> 00:33:53.080 align:middle line:84%
And those souls usually
come from one location

00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:54.680 align:middle line:90%
in the universe.

00:33:54.680 --> 00:33:57.110 align:middle line:90%
So now what people ask me a lot.

00:33:57.110 --> 00:33:58.220 align:middle line:90%
So I guide a regression.

00:33:58.220 --> 00:34:00.250 align:middle line:84%
The client learns
they're interplanetary.

00:34:00.250 --> 00:34:04.327 align:middle line:84%
And they know or we figure
out through the regression,

00:34:04.327 --> 00:34:06.410 align:middle line:84%
let's just say the oldest
child is their daughter,

00:34:06.410 --> 00:34:07.940 align:middle line:90%
and the daughter is Earth-based.

00:34:07.940 --> 00:34:10.760 align:middle line:84%
So the client-- this
is a common question.

00:34:10.760 --> 00:34:15.080 align:middle line:84%
The client asks me, so
does that mean my daughter,

00:34:15.080 --> 00:34:18.639 align:middle line:84%
Earth-based daughter
is in my soul pod?

00:34:18.639 --> 00:34:21.380 align:middle line:90%
I explain, no, they are not.

00:34:21.380 --> 00:34:24.580 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes that
bothers people.

00:34:24.580 --> 00:34:27.010 align:middle line:84%
And so just so the
listeners understand this.

00:34:27.010 --> 00:34:30.030 align:middle line:84%
But the bottom line is
an interplanetary soul

00:34:30.030 --> 00:34:33.960 align:middle line:84%
can have an Earth-based
family member

00:34:33.960 --> 00:34:37.290 align:middle line:84%
or loved one that they've
had multiple lives with.

00:34:37.290 --> 00:34:39.489 align:middle line:90%
There's still a soul connection.

00:34:39.489 --> 00:34:42.370 align:middle line:84%
It's just not that
they're in the same pod.

00:34:42.370 --> 00:34:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Why are the pods so
small with the interplanetaries?

00:34:46.050 --> 00:34:49.440 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: Partly because
interplanetary souls can come

00:34:49.440 --> 00:34:52.239 align:middle line:84%
from so many places
in the universe,

00:34:52.239 --> 00:35:00.600 align:middle line:84%
that often there are not many
souls from their home location

00:35:00.600 --> 00:35:02.310 align:middle line:90%
with whom they incarnate.

00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:05.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And who they have
those basic vibrational

00:35:05.010 --> 00:35:06.460 align:middle line:90%
frequencies that match with.

00:35:06.460 --> 00:35:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Exactly.

00:35:07.260 --> 00:35:10.000 align:middle line:84%
And they don't know
them in current life,

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:12.570 align:middle line:84%
perhaps, because
sometimes I work

00:35:12.570 --> 00:35:15.510 align:middle line:84%
with an interplanetary
client who

00:35:15.510 --> 00:35:21.100 align:middle line:84%
is the only soul from their home
location that comes to Earth.

00:35:21.100 --> 00:35:21.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:35:21.900 --> 00:35:22.992 align:middle line:90%
I hear you.

00:35:22.992 --> 00:35:27.540 align:middle line:84%
And for them, oftentimes, it's
a little lonelier existence?

00:35:27.540 --> 00:35:29.490 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: I would say yes.

00:35:29.490 --> 00:35:32.150 align:middle line:84%
Truthfully, I think
interplanetary souls

00:35:32.150 --> 00:35:35.750 align:middle line:84%
and angelic souls, maybe a
bit more interplanetary souls

00:35:35.750 --> 00:35:38.210 align:middle line:84%
struggle a bit more
with loneliness

00:35:38.210 --> 00:35:40.575 align:middle line:90%
than Earth-based souls do.

00:35:40.575 --> 00:35:42.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, let's go
to the angelic souls.

00:35:42.450 --> 00:35:43.250 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yeah.

00:35:43.250 --> 00:35:46.170 align:middle line:84%
Angelic souls-- all three
types of souls are fascinating.

00:35:46.170 --> 00:35:52.010 align:middle line:84%
But angelic souls are, I
find, incredibly fascinating.

00:35:52.010 --> 00:35:54.950 align:middle line:84%
I have a new book that will
have a lot more angelic soul

00:35:54.950 --> 00:35:57.440 align:middle line:90%
information in it from clients.

00:35:57.440 --> 00:36:01.680 align:middle line:84%
Angelic souls are some
of the most loving,

00:36:01.680 --> 00:36:05.910 align:middle line:84%
nurturing, caring because they
come from the angelic realm.

00:36:05.910 --> 00:36:08.540 align:middle line:90%
So angelic souls serve source.

00:36:08.540 --> 00:36:10.440 align:middle line:90%
They carry source energy.

00:36:10.440 --> 00:36:15.560 align:middle line:84%
So their signature vibration,
their signature orientation

00:36:15.560 --> 00:36:21.180 align:middle line:84%
is some of the purest caring
that I often ever see in people.

00:36:21.180 --> 00:36:28.020 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing how they are so
accepting of so many people that

00:36:28.020 --> 00:36:29.850 align:middle line:90%
are around them.

00:36:29.850 --> 00:36:32.500 align:middle line:84%
There are more angelic
souls coming to the planet.

00:36:32.500 --> 00:36:35.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I was going
to be my next question.

00:36:35.470 --> 00:36:37.810 align:middle line:84%
So that hallmark is
they're very caring.

00:36:37.810 --> 00:36:40.350 align:middle line:90%
What about their soul pods?

00:36:40.350 --> 00:36:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: The soul
pods are small,

00:36:42.130 --> 00:36:44.590 align:middle line:90%
just like interplanetary souls.

00:36:44.590 --> 00:36:46.960 align:middle line:90%
Again, it could be two souls.

00:36:46.960 --> 00:36:48.113 align:middle line:90%
It could be five souls.

00:36:48.113 --> 00:36:50.730 align:middle line:90%


00:36:50.730 --> 00:36:54.630 align:middle line:84%
Angelic souls work within
the quandary of souls

00:36:54.630 --> 00:36:56.110 align:middle line:90%
that are angelic souls.

00:36:56.110 --> 00:37:00.570 align:middle line:84%
And they're headed
by the archangels.

00:37:00.570 --> 00:37:03.190 align:middle line:84%
But they don't-- it's not
like they don't have karma.

00:37:03.190 --> 00:37:05.580 align:middle line:90%
They can gather karma.

00:37:05.580 --> 00:37:09.450 align:middle line:84%
But typically they
are so accepting

00:37:09.450 --> 00:37:11.760 align:middle line:84%
that they don't
have quite as much

00:37:11.760 --> 00:37:15.330 align:middle line:90%
to work on in a human lifetime.

00:37:15.330 --> 00:37:16.690 align:middle line:90%
They're highly unique.

00:37:16.690 --> 00:37:19.600 align:middle line:84%
But we need their
energy on this planet.

00:37:19.600 --> 00:37:23.420 align:middle line:84%
We need more acceptance
of each other

00:37:23.420 --> 00:37:27.320 align:middle line:84%
and people's behavior and
people's differences and all

00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:28.225 align:middle line:90%
of that.

00:37:28.225 --> 00:37:30.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, and that's
one thing you're finding

00:37:30.350 --> 00:37:33.260 align:middle line:84%
in your work, is this going
toward this larger acceptance

00:37:33.260 --> 00:37:38.150 align:middle line:84%
and moving into what floats
all of us instead of the--

00:37:38.150 --> 00:37:40.620 align:middle line:84%
and everybody I interview,
it's the same thing.

00:37:40.620 --> 00:37:45.250 align:middle line:84%
We have to move away from
competition, exclusiveness, et

00:37:45.250 --> 00:37:46.220 align:middle line:90%
cetera.

00:37:46.220 --> 00:37:50.460 align:middle line:84%
We can't isolate ourselves as
beings, as a country, as souls.

00:37:50.460 --> 00:37:51.750 align:middle line:90%
We can't do that any longer.

00:37:51.750 --> 00:37:55.580 align:middle line:84%
So with the souls
that you're seeing,

00:37:55.580 --> 00:38:00.270 align:middle line:84%
you're seeing an increase in
angelic souls incarnating now.

00:38:00.270 --> 00:38:03.260 align:middle line:90%
What about IP souls?

00:38:03.260 --> 00:38:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yes.

00:38:04.970 --> 00:38:10.296 align:middle line:84%
Even though Earth is about
90% Earth-based souls,

00:38:10.296 --> 00:38:13.940 align:middle line:84%
but more angelics
and more IP souls

00:38:13.940 --> 00:38:16.710 align:middle line:84%
are being prepared
also to come to Earth.

00:38:16.710 --> 00:38:17.790 align:middle line:90%
So what does that mean?

00:38:17.790 --> 00:38:23.380 align:middle line:84%
That means IPs and angelic
souls have difficulty at times

00:38:23.380 --> 00:38:24.380 align:middle line:90%
being here.

00:38:24.380 --> 00:38:26.480 align:middle line:90%
It's an unfamiliar environment.

00:38:26.480 --> 00:38:31.220 align:middle line:84%
It's an unfamiliar physical
body, unfamiliar diet.

00:38:31.220 --> 00:38:33.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which can bring
a lot of dietary issues,

00:38:33.620 --> 00:38:36.650 align:middle line:84%
digestive issues,
sleeping issues.

00:38:36.650 --> 00:38:38.420 align:middle line:84%
These souls have
a hard time here.

00:38:38.420 --> 00:38:39.460 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Absolutely.

00:38:39.460 --> 00:38:45.320 align:middle line:84%
IPs can contribute in so
many ways to our culture,

00:38:45.320 --> 00:38:49.300 align:middle line:84%
but they can also struggle
so much with being here

00:38:49.300 --> 00:38:55.780 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps have ideas
that we might say need

00:38:55.780 --> 00:39:02.120 align:middle line:84%
to be molded a bit or
calmed a bit or whatever.

00:39:02.120 --> 00:39:08.330 align:middle line:84%
But humanity, humanity is a
work in progress, as we know.

00:39:08.330 --> 00:39:12.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this place
in our collective history,

00:39:12.290 --> 00:39:15.010 align:middle line:84%
it seems to me, as the
time the windows opening

00:39:15.010 --> 00:39:21.400 align:middle line:84%
for the return to a sense of
basic justice, basic morality.

00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.200 align:middle line:84%
And I don't mean that
in a churchy sense.

00:39:23.200 --> 00:39:26.830 align:middle line:84%
Basic kindness and
respect for one another.

00:39:26.830 --> 00:39:29.070 align:middle line:84%
And so what are you seeing
with the souls coming in

00:39:29.070 --> 00:39:31.320 align:middle line:84%
and the children of
the people you're

00:39:31.320 --> 00:39:34.260 align:middle line:84%
regressing in terms of the
nature of these kids that

00:39:34.260 --> 00:39:35.260 align:middle line:90%
are coming in now.

00:39:35.260 --> 00:39:37.840 align:middle line:84%
In terms of being more
about the collective,

00:39:37.840 --> 00:39:39.980 align:middle line:84%
are you seeing that
trend happening?

00:39:39.980 --> 00:39:40.780 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Some.

00:39:40.780 --> 00:39:43.950 align:middle line:90%


00:39:43.950 --> 00:39:50.280 align:middle line:84%
I think that humanity is
at a point of almost trying

00:39:50.280 --> 00:39:53.290 align:middle line:84%
to figure out, which
direction are we going?

00:39:53.290 --> 00:39:55.290 align:middle line:84%
Are we becoming more
inclusive or are we

00:39:55.290 --> 00:39:57.720 align:middle line:90%
becoming more exclusive?

00:39:57.720 --> 00:40:00.880 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I certainly see
a lot of young people,

00:40:00.880 --> 00:40:06.690 align:middle line:90%
young people meaning 18 to 25.

00:40:06.690 --> 00:40:10.440 align:middle line:84%
I see a lot of
advanced young people.

00:40:10.440 --> 00:40:14.517 align:middle line:84%
But I also see young people that
don't quite know where they fit.

00:40:14.517 --> 00:40:15.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Because they're young.

00:40:15.850 --> 00:40:19.320 align:middle line:84%
One of one of the people I
interviewed who does Vedic

00:40:19.320 --> 00:40:23.310 align:middle line:84%
astrology and handwriting was
saying the interesting thing

00:40:23.310 --> 00:40:30.450 align:middle line:84%
about Gen Zs, for example, is
that their backbone is to have

00:40:30.450 --> 00:40:36.360 align:middle line:84%
strong character, high
moralistic character and strong

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:40.723 align:middle line:84%
will, but they don't really
mature until their 40s.

00:40:40.723 --> 00:40:43.990 align:middle line:90%


00:40:43.990 --> 00:40:45.790 align:middle line:90%
The oldest is 27 right now.

00:40:45.790 --> 00:40:47.580 align:middle line:84%
I just find that
really interesting

00:40:47.580 --> 00:40:49.870 align:middle line:84%
as a generational
statement if that's true,

00:40:49.870 --> 00:40:51.952 align:middle line:84%
that archetypally,
they want to bring back

00:40:51.952 --> 00:40:53.535 align:middle line:84%
a sense of inclusiveness
and morality.

00:40:53.535 --> 00:40:55.030 align:middle line:90%
But they're still kids.

00:40:55.030 --> 00:40:57.660 align:middle line:84%
They're still on their
games and such right now.

00:40:57.660 --> 00:40:58.770 align:middle line:90%
>> LINDA: Yes.

00:40:58.770 --> 00:41:00.310 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I think that's true.

00:41:00.310 --> 00:41:05.970 align:middle line:84%
But I also see some young people
like undergraduate college age

00:41:05.970 --> 00:41:12.120 align:middle line:84%
young people that are amazingly
advanced and amazingly smart

00:41:12.120 --> 00:41:18.050 align:middle line:84%
and creating new
ideas, new skills,

00:41:18.050 --> 00:41:19.340 align:middle line:90%
new ways of functioning--

00:41:19.340 --> 00:41:20.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:41:20.140 --> 00:41:21.560 align:middle line:84%
So some of them
are already awake.

00:41:21.560 --> 00:41:23.360 align:middle line:84%
The rest is going to take
a little longer to wake up,

00:41:23.360 --> 00:41:24.500 align:middle line:90%
it sounds like.

00:41:24.500 --> 00:41:25.923 align:middle line:90%
So I have a question.

00:41:25.923 --> 00:41:27.340 align:middle line:84%
The ones that
you're seeing in who

00:41:27.340 --> 00:41:30.340 align:middle line:84%
are appearing to be very already
awake and advanced and creative

00:41:30.340 --> 00:41:33.490 align:middle line:84%
and bringing these new
technologies, ideas, thoughts

00:41:33.490 --> 00:41:35.890 align:middle line:84%
to the planet, are
they Earth-based souls

00:41:35.890 --> 00:41:37.750 align:middle line:84%
who are simply coming
into a field that's

00:41:37.750 --> 00:41:39.670 align:middle line:90%
more ripe to express that?

00:41:39.670 --> 00:41:42.760 align:middle line:84%
Or are they more IP
souls that are coming in

00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:46.893 align:middle line:84%
with these ideas and knowledge
to help advance us this time?

00:41:46.893 --> 00:41:48.560 align:middle line:84%
>> LINDA: Yeah, that's
a great question.

00:41:48.560 --> 00:41:50.360 align:middle line:90%
And I'm seeing honestly both.

00:41:50.360 --> 00:41:51.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Good.

